## 3. Component Guidelines (Shadcn + cva)

- All UI components in `apps/web/src/components/ui/` must use the theme colors and spacing.
- Use `class-variance-authority (cva)` for variant-based styling (see `button.tsx`).
- **Default variants:** `primary` (default), `secondary`, `destructive`, `outline`, `ghost`, `link`.
- **Size variants:** `sm`, `md` (default), `lg`, `icon`.

### Example: Button Variants
```typescript
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-all disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        primary: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
        secondary: "bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80",
        destructive: "bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90",
        outline: "border bg-background hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground",
        ghost: "hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground",
        link: "text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline",
      },
      size: {
        sm: "h-8 px-3",
        md: "h-9 px-4 py-2",
        lg: "h-10 px-6",
        icon: "size-9",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "primary",
      size: "md",
    },
  }
)
```

### Usage Example
```tsx
<Button variant="destructive" size="lg">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="secondary">Cancel</Button>
```

- **Always use the `cn` utility** for merging classes.
- **Do not hardcode colors**; use theme variables or Tailwind classes.
- For new components, follow the same variant/size pattern.
- For hero/login backgrounds, you may use decorative blobs with the following pattern:
  - Absolutely positioned, blurred, and animated using the theme blob colors.
  - Use the CSS classes: `bg-[#fecaca]`, `bg-[#fed7aa]`, `bg-[#e2e8f0]`, `blur-xl`, `mix-blend-multiply`, and custom keyframes for fade-in and blob movement.
  - See the login page for a full example.
- All input and form fields must:
  - Use theme tokens for border, focus, placeholder, and icon color (see globals.css).
  - Never use browser default blue for focus or border.
  - Reference the utility classes and CSS in globals.css for placeholder and icon color.

